<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     02-16 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Names News Editor For South Carolina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eva M. Parziale, correspondent in charge of
The Associated Press bureau in Portland, Maine, has been named the
AP's news editor for South Carolina.
   The appointment was announced by Columbia Chief of Bureau John
Shurr.
   Ms. Parziale, 28, joined the AP in San Francisco in 1984. She
earned a master's degree at Columbia University and rejoined the AP
in Miami in 1985. She became Portland correspondent in 1987.
   A native of Euclid, Ohio, Ms. Parziale is a graduate of Bowling
Green State University and began her journalism career with the Lake
County Telegraph in Painesville, Ohio.
</TEXT>
