<HEAD>Dollar Up Slightly, Stocks Off Fractionally</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar rebounded slightly against the Japanese
yen Thursday, while the Tokyo Stock Exchange's leading index fell
back from its latest record high.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues lost 65.90
points, or 0.20 percent, closing at 32,083.58, despite a gain in
morning trading. The index had climbed 166.59 points to a record
32,149.48 finish Wednesday.
