German central bank council meeting later Thursday, said a dealer
with Mitsubishi Bank in Tokyo.
   He said the dollar is unlikely to move much while there is any
chance that the Bundesbank will raise its discount or Lombard rates.
   Market players stepped off to the sidelines also because of
uncertainties over the U.S. trade figures, the dealer added.
