<HEAD>Gunmen Injure Five In Attack on Protestant Bar</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout to ADD claim of responsibility. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen burst into a Protestant
clubhouse in Belfast today and opened fire with automatic weapons,
injuring five people, police said. An extremist splinter of the IRA
claimed responsibility.
   The incident occurred at midday at the Orange Cross Social Club,
a drinking spot in the predominantly Protestant Shankill district,
police said.
   A witness told London Broadcasting Corp. radio that three
attackers lined up some men against the bar and opened fire with
Kalashnikov assault rifles.
   ``They singled out a few men on the premises, put them against
the bar, and started to shoot indiscriminately,'' said the witness,
who was not identified.
   Nearby Mater Hospital said it admitted one man in very serious
condition with head injuries and two with serious chest wounds. Two
women were in stable condition with stomach injuries.
   The Irish National Liberation Army, a small offshoot of the
predominantly Catholic Irish Republican Army, claimed responsibility
in a statement to Belfast news media, saying it was avenging recent
attacks on Catholics.
   Protestant extremists claimed responsibility for the shooting
deaths of Tony Fusco, a Belfast businessman with no known political
links; and Patrick Finucane, who was prominent as an attorney for
IRA suspects.
   Also this week, gunmen killed John Joe Davey, a member of the
Magherafelt town council for Sinn Fein, the outlawed IRA's political
wing. No claim of responsibility was made.
   The IRA is fighting to end British rule in Northern Ireland and
unite the province with the overwhelmingly Catholic Irish Republic.
   The Irish National Liberation Army, formed by disaffected IRA
members in the 1970s, has been reduced in size by an internal feud
but is believed to retain a handful of armed activists.
   After the attack, a van was found burning outside Divis Flats, a
Catholic-populated tenement block, and police said they were
investigating whether it was hijacked by the gunmen.
