<HEAD>Moscow Rock Concert a Rip-Off, Fans Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Italian rock star Sabrina failed to impress
Moscow fans who paid up to $9 for a concert and ended up with only
six or seven songs in a 30-minute appearance, a newspaper reported
Thursday.
   At least 11 spectators at the Wednesday night concert were
injured when thousands of fans crowded onto a dance floor to get a
glimpse of the singer, the official Tass news agency said.
   The newspaper Moskovsky Komsomolets said Sabrina arrived in
Moscow amid fanfare usually reserved for a real ``superstar,''
including six limousines, eight back-up sedans, a luxury suite at
the Cosmos Hotel and 70 bodyguards.
   ``Before the first show, Italians were strictly guarding and
nobody could lay a finger on Sabrina's equipment,'' the newspaper
said.
   With 22,000 fans waiting at the Olympic Hall, she failed to show
up on time, ``first washing her hair, then demanding a telephone
call to Italy and a vase with fruit and towels in her dressing
room,'' the newspaper said.
   ``After Sabrina appeared on the stage, the initial madness of
fans was replaced by a strange silence _ at first she sang some of
her own songs, then sensing the lack of enthusiasm, started to
repeat some old songs from the repetoires of some popular groups,''
the newspaper said. ``After 30 minutes, the concert was over.''
   As the fans left the concert hall, many were heard to mutter,
``Deceit!'' and ``Swindle!'' the newspaper's critic said.
   Noting the ticket prices of about $6.50 to $9 for six or seven
songs, ``isn't that a bit too expensive?'' the critic said.
   Tass said the 11 fans were injured ``when thousands of spectators
flooded the dance floor near the stage to catch a glimpse of the
curvaceous singer.''
   The news agency did not say if any of the injuries was serious.
