<TEXT>
   President Bush on Thursday made a pitch for
Atlanta to be the host for the summer Olympic Games in 1996.
   Bush met briefly with Juan Antonio Samaranch of Spain, president
of the International Olympic Committee, and representatives of an
Atlanta group promoting the Southern city for the event.
