<HEAD>Bush Calls on Soviets Not to Interfere in Afghanistan</HEAD>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TERENCE HUNT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP White House Correspondent</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush today called upon the Soviet
Union to refrain from interfering in Afghanistan now that Red Army
troops have departed and said he hoped the country could come
together ``with no more bloodbaths.''
   The president also expressed reservations about an agreement
reached by five Central American presidents to disarm the Contra
