<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Unemployment     02-16 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Unemployment,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rate Falls to 7 Percent, Total Number Lowest Since 1981</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Britain fell to a seasonally
adjusted 7 percent of the workforce in January from 7.2 percent in
December, bringing the total number of jobless to its lowest level
in eight years, the government said Thursday.
   The figure was down from 8.9 percent in January 1988, the
Department of Employment said.
   Total seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 1,988,000
people in January, the lowest total since January 1981, and
confirmed widespread expectations that the figure would be below the
2 million-mark.
   It compared with a revised 2,037,000 people in December and
2,519,000 people in January 1988.
</TEXT>
