compared with last week's 94,196 and last year's 85,485.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,033 cars this week, up from
21,069 a week ago but down from last year's 22,786.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 22,067, compared
with 21,652 a week ago and 18,385 in the same week last year.
