<FIRST>r f AM-Premiere-Murdoch     02-16 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Premiere-Murdoch,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Murdoch Agrees to Buy Hachette's Stake in Premiere Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rupert Murdoch's News Corp. Ltd. has agreed to
buy the half-interest held by the French publisher Hachette Group in
their 50-50 joint venture that publishes Premiere magazine, the
companies said Thursday.
   Terms were not disclosed. The sale is subject to federal
regulatory approval.
   Premiere was launched 18 months ago to cover all aspects of the
movie business for general readers and has a circulation of more
than 400,000.
   The deal comes about 3{ months after Murdoch's company completed
the sale to Hachette of its half-interest in their Elle fashion
magazine joint ventures in the United States and the United Kingdom.
Terms of that deal were also not disclosed, but the price was
reportedly about $150 million.
   News Corp's half-interest in the Premiere magazine venture is
held by its News America Publishing Inc., which publishes newspapers
and magazines and has filmed entertainment and television operations
in the United States.
   Hachette controls its stake in Premiere magazine through Hachette
Publications Inc., whose main business is publishing magazines in
the United States.
