<HEAD>Pepperell Extends Deadline for Bids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST POINT, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   West Point-Pepperell Inc. said Thursday it
had extended its deadline for buyout proposals until next Tuesday.
   Pepperell's announcement came a day after Farley Inc. of Chicago
extended its $1.53 billion offer for the Georgia-based textile
company until midnight Friday.
   Pepperell said it would not reveal the identity of any bidders or
the nature of any bids received so far.
   The company's directors had declared a noon Wednesday deadline
when they put Pepperell up for sale Feb. 3, saying they believed
Farley's $52-per-share cash offer was too low.
   The latest deadline for bids is noon EST on Tuesday.
   In a letter to shareholders filed with the Securities and
Exchange Commission, Pepperell said it would withhold any comment on
the bidding process _ which it said includes several interested
parties _ until ``after an agreement in principle or definitive
agreement is entered into between the company and a prospective
purchaser.
   ``Until then, the process will be deemed to be continuing,'' the
letter said.
