<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-UnitedTelecom     02-16 0347</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-United Telecom,0357</SECOND>
<HEAD>United Telecom, Major Owner Of US Sprint, Reports Earnings Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   United Telecommunications Inc., the
majority owner of US Sprint Communications Co., said Thursday its
earnings shot up in the fourth quarter because of a one-time gain
from operations it sold.
   United Telecom also said US Sprint's results improved sharply in
the quarter. The nation's third-biggest long-distance company had
its first positive operating income except for a one-time charge for
restructuring, United Telecom said.
   United Telecom assumed management control of US Sprint in July
1988 and purchased controlling interest from its former 50-50
partner, GTE Corp., on Jan. 3 of this year.
   ``This has been a year of extaordinary change and outstanding
progress for United Telecom, a year in which we started to realized
the positive results of our long-term strategy,'' William T. Esrey,
the president, said in a statement.
   The company said it earned $379.5 million, or $3.70 a share, in
the quarter, up from $29.1 million, or 29 cents a share, a year
earlier. Revenue jumped to $1.73 billion from $780 million. US
Sprint's revenue was not included in the year-earlier period.
   The bulk of the quarterly profit came from an after-tax gain of
$369 million, which was mainly from the sale of the company's
cellular and paging operations. That gain wsa partially offset by an
after-tax loss of $64 million charge consisting of United Telecom's
share of a restructuring charge at US Sprint.
   For all of 1988, United Telecom said net income improved to a
record $508.9 million, or $4.95 a share, from a loss of $51.5
million the previous year.
   In 1988, United Telecom had consolidated net revenues of $6.5
billion, compared with $2.9 billion in 1987 when Sprint's revenues
of $2.7 billion were not included.
   Esrey said US Sprint had long-distance revenue of $3.4 billion in
1988, up 27 percent from $2.67 billion the year before. Including
the $195 million business restructuring charge, US Sprint had an
operating loss of $181 million for the fourth quarter and $409
million for the year in 1988.
</TEXT>
