<HEAD>Campbell Releases Second Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Campbell Soup Co. reported Thursday its
second-quarter earnings rose 12 percent on sales gains in all of its
divisions.
   Campbell said it earned $94.9 million, or 73 cents a share,
compared to $84.6 million, or 65 cents per share, during the same
period last year.
   The Camden-based company said its sales rose to $1.58 billion in
the quarter ended Jan. 29 from $1.34 billion a year earlier.
   ``All of Campbell's operating divisions _ Campbell U.S.A.,
Campbell International, Pepperidge Farm and Campbell Enterprise _
scored impressive sales and operating earning gains despite
increased cost pressures affecting the ingredients and packaging,''
Campbell President R. Gordon McGovern said in a news release.
   Earnings for the first half of Campbell's fiscal year totaled
$164.2 million or $1.27 per share, compared to $179.5 million, or
$1.38 a share, in the first six months of last year.
   The year-earlier results included a $32.5 million after-tax gain
for a change in the company's accounting for income taxes.
   Sales for the first six months increased to $2.92 billion from
$2.52 billion last year.
